snippet.textDisplay:
07:00

Jaswal says "nautanki re na dani teri" while the captions read "nautanki re man mani teri".

Personally I think it should've been what the captions read as that had been the pattern prior to reaching this point. In another words, the pattern had been "na dani teri" followed by "man mani teri". Even the background singers were singing "man mani teri".

The captions are correct and I think Jaswal made a mistake.

Please correct me if I am wrong.

Having said all that, this is undoubtedly one of my favorite songs. Great work Coke Studio!

snippet.textDisplay: Saying to all Indian listeners and also  from other countries, appreciating CSP superb performances. Very well written thoughts by you for us all good people in India, Pakistan and the world. I have lived out of Pakistan since age 22 and my grown sons here in the US have very good and decent friends from school age of Indian descent. My oldest son keeps on saying that even being Kashmiri Muslims our ancestor must have converted from Hinduism.  Anyhow, we are the same people and must be together and appreciate each other and remove the British practice of "Divide and Conquer". Please read the book, "Observations, Perceptions & Questions".
